<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idf68d99f0-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s10503"><num value="10503">§ 10503.</num><heading> Exhibiting merchant mariners’ documents</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Before signing the agreement required by <ref href="/us/usc/t46/s10502">section 10502 of this title</ref>, a seaman required by <ref href="/us/usc/t46/s8701">section 8701 of this title</ref> to have a merchant mariner’s document shall exhibit to the master a document issued to the seaman and appropriately endorsed for the capacity in which the seaman is to serve.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idf68d99f1-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5">(<ref href="/us/pl/98/89">Pub. L. 98–89</ref>, <date date="1983-08-26">Aug. 26, 1983</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/97/570">97 Stat. 570</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
